      Subinterfaces of Constraint in com.sri.ai.grinder.sgdpllt.api 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  Context
      A Context combines a Registry and a Constraint in order to provide a context for SGDPLL(T)-related methods.
      interface  SingleVariableConstraint
      An Expression with efficient internal representation for incrementally deciding satisfiability of a boolean formulas on literals in a certain theory.
      Methods in com.sri.ai.grinder.sgdpllt.api that return Constraint 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      default Constraint Constraint.conjoin(Expression formula, Context context)
      Returns an SGDPLLTTester representing the conjunction of this constraint and a given formula, or null if they are contradictory.
      default Constraint Constraint.conjoinWithConjunctiveClause(Expression conjunctiveClause, Context context)
      Returns the result of conjoining this constraint with all literal conjuncts of a given conjunctive clause (note that if conjunction is not an application of and, it will be considered a unit conjunction with itself the only conjunct.
      Constraint Constraint.conjoinWithLiteral(Expression literal, Context context)
      Returns an SGDPLLTTester representing the conjunction of this constraint and a given literal, or null if they are contradictory.
      Constraint Constraint.makeContradiction()
      Make contradictory version of this constraint; this means the contradiction is of the same "type" as this contradiction (for example, same theory, among other details), but is a contradiction.
      default Constraint Theory.makeTrueConstraint()
      Returns a new true (empty conjunction) constraint for this theory.

      class  AbstractSingleVariableConstraint
      An abstract Expression with efficient internal representation for a conjunction in a given theory.

      An implementation of AbstractSingleVariableConstraint for theories in which there is interaction between normalized atoms.

      An extension of AbstractSingleVariableConstraint for theories in which there is no interaction between distinct normalized atoms.

      A multi-variable context that detects unsatisfiability insofar as the single-variable constraint theories detect it themselves.
      class  DefaultMultiVariableConstraint
      An Constraint on multiple variables.
      class  MultiVariableContextWithCheckedProperty
      An Context on multiple variables, with the ability to ensure all single-variable constraints that are part of it have a property determined by a ExpressionStepSolver, or otherwise the total constraint is deemed unsatisfiable.
